	   <tr><td colspan=2>After reading many of these posts i find a few flaws in some of what people are saying.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>For one the High lvl Bear form spell is a quest spell. <br><br>Once the shaman gets the companion spirit,(pet) this becomes most useful. Our pets are not the best in game but they are not meant to. They save our butts and do ext dmg when we solo and group.<br><br>When you solo, you pull with either slow or dot and bring mob to pet and have it attack. Then you root and sit and med a bit while pet keeps mob occupid. Dot again and root and sit. Keep eye on pets health during this time also. <br><br>Being agnostic has not caused me any problems so far. lvl 48 atm. Barb shaman can be aimable very easy. its called faction.  I have even seen DE's become indifferent in some cities due to alot of hard work on faction. So do not think that a barb shaman will be KoS in any city other than that of the DE,Orge,Troll cities. I have not found a way to raise faction in those 3 cities. But that is only 3 out of what 100+ places to buy and sell. And almost that many places to bank as well.<br><br>In one post he said that shaman are a melee class.  This is NOT true.  Shaman do not melee at higher lvls.  We do not tank. Yes we can pull. But we are a caster class.  We have more HP than all the other caster classes but that is it.  It allows us to take more hits and if you are good enough, even cast a few when being hit.  A pure caster can not do this.  A pure caster will also be killed in less than 1/2 the hits that a shaman can take.  Any class of shaman.  We melee at low lvls because our DD are not enough to take down a mob. But in a group we are the healer at the lower lvls.  Plain and simple.  At the higher lvls we are THE BUFF class! We have the best BUFFS in the game overall!  I have yet to find someone that does not want a shammy buff on a plain raid! And our slow is awesome!  <br>We have our downfalls but all classes do. But out of my 14+ race/class choices I think the shaman is<br>a very needed class in any group at any lvl.  We can do just about everything every other caster class can do but ports and rezzes.  <br><br>And the Barbarian shaman is the BEST choice because of its higher wisdom base to start with.  Shaman do not need the strenght of an Orge or Troll.  Remember we are NOT a melee class! We are CASTERS!<br><br>I also noticed that no one mentioned the fact that the shaman can also Debuff mobs!  We not only nuke,dot and buff we can Debuff!  So whats not to like about a shaman?  NOTHING!<br><br>SHAMANess will rule the day!<br><br>BTW one more thing. Put as much as you can into wisdom when you start. If you dont you WILL regret it at higher lvls.  We can heal after 30. No not as well as the cleric. But that is the clerics MAIN job, to heal. We are a cross between the cleric and the necro and the druid.  We have much the same type spells they have AND we have the HP to take the hits!<br><br>Just my 2cp worth of info <br>/bow<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
